WEBVTT

00:06.964 --> 00:09.693
Okay, Mike, I just stepped
on a fork in the tub.

00:09.693 --> 00:11.347
How many times have we told the kids,

00:11.348 --> 00:14.631
we wash spoons in the tub,
knives and forks in the bathroom sink?

00:14.632 --> 00:15.661
It's just common sense.

00:15.662 --> 00:18.722
[Sighs] This is crazy.
We can't go on like this.

00:18.723 --> 00:21.210
We need a silverware caddy in the shower.

00:21.211 --> 00:23.094
I might have something
in the garage we can use.

00:23.095 --> 00:24.509
How 'bout that old ice bucket that says,

00:24.510 --> 00:26.685
- "it's 5:00 somewhere"?
- Oh, you know what?

00:26.686 --> 00:30.519
Since the dishwasher's not working right now,
we could use the caddy from there.

00:30.520 --> 00:33.314
We'll just hang it on the showerhead
where the shampoo thing usually goes.

00:33.315 --> 00:34.326
That would be perfect!

00:34.327 --> 00:36.847
Are you sad right now? 'Cause I'm really sad.

00:36.848 --> 00:40.550
Look. I know we wanted to save money,
and we gave it our best shot,

00:40.551 --> 00:43.537
but despite how much I'm gonna
miss this whole hose situation,

00:43.538 --> 00:45.899
- it's time to fix the sink.
- Mm.

00:46.657 --> 00:51.572
- Gorillas... tigers...
- Should we ask?

00:51.573 --> 00:54.613
If we don't, it'll just look
bad when the school calls.

00:54.614 --> 00:56.486
Okay, what's going on, Brick?

00:56.487 --> 01:01.303
Tigers... lions... Tarzan...

01:01.304 --> 01:03.456
Why are you telling us
things that are in a jungle?

01:03.457 --> 01:05.041
Ding, ding, ding, ding, ding, ding, ding!

01:05.042 --> 01:07.071
I was online doing research
for my pyramid paper,

01:07.072 --> 01:09.809
and I found something
called "The $25,000 Pyramid."

01:09.810 --> 01:13.631
Then I started watching
other game shows. Fascinating.

01:13.632 --> 01:14.619
My favorite's "Match Game."

01:14.620 --> 01:17.964
Have you heard of Nipsy Russell?
Hi-larious.

01:17.965 --> 01:20.439
And Adrienne Barbeau...
That is one foxy lady.

01:20.440 --> 01:22.303
- Mm-hmm.
- And they were all having so much fun

01:22.304 --> 01:23.576
at a time when things were tough.

01:23.577 --> 01:25.396
Seems like we could use a
little of that around here.

01:25.397 --> 01:27.528
I stepped on a fork in my bathtub.

01:27.529 --> 01:29.585
- This is what I'm saying.
- [Door opens]

01:29.586 --> 01:31.032
[Door closes]

01:31.033 --> 01:31.879
You're not gonna believe this.

01:31.880 --> 01:34.443
They're cutting back my hours at Spudsy's.

01:34.444 --> 01:35.961
What? Why?

01:35.962 --> 01:39.118
Corporate is putting
in a "self-fixin's" bar.

01:39.119 --> 01:40.611
It's outrageous!

01:40.612 --> 01:42.354
Civilians can't do it like us.

01:42.355 --> 01:44.822
Do you know how easy it
is to overwhelm a potato

01:44.823 --> 01:45.674
with scallions?

01:45.675 --> 01:47.939
Let me end the suspense for you... very.

01:47.940 --> 01:50.143
- Oh, Sue, I'm sorry.
- Tough break.

01:50.144 --> 01:52.076
Mike, weren't you just
saying that you needed someone

01:52.077 --> 01:54.017
- to help you at the quarry?
- Bah, bah, bah, bah, bah, bah.

01:54.018 --> 01:55.447
I'll take it. I don't care what it is.

01:55.448 --> 01:56.878
I'll do it. [Gasps] Do I get a name tag?

01:56.879 --> 01:58.708
How 'bout a cubicle? Doesn't matter. I'm in.

01:58.709 --> 02:00.612
Sue, trust me, you're not even gonna want it.

02:00.613 --> 02:02.956
It's... it's cleaning
up around the trailers...

02:02.957 --> 02:05.249
Mopping, sweeping, throwing out the trash,

02:05.250 --> 02:06.253
cleaning the toilet.

02:06.254 --> 02:09.547
- Keep talkin'.
- Look, family working together is a bad idea.

02:09.548 --> 02:11.507
[Sighs] You know how I feel about nepotism.

02:11.508 --> 02:13.692
[Scoffs] You're letting
her clean your toilets.

02:13.693 --> 02:16.574
- You're not giving her a part in your movie.
- Oh, my God, Dad.

02:16.575 --> 02:18.067
This would be so perfect.

02:18.068 --> 02:19.871
You'll get to see another side of me.

02:19.872 --> 02:21.595
I'll get to see another side of you.

02:21.596 --> 02:24.230
- This is no other side of me.
- We could commute together.

02:24.231 --> 02:28.774
I'm capable, I'm motivated,
and I'm really, really excited.

02:28.775 --> 02:31.118
Please, Daddy, please!

02:31.119 --> 02:33.158
It would be my honor to clean your toilets.

02:33.159 --> 02:34.453
[Sighs]

02:38.310 --> 02:41.181
Well, I might have an
extra sink in the backyard.

02:41.182 --> 02:46.254
Only got 17 at the moment,
but I guess I can let one go.

02:46.255 --> 02:47.654
I appreciate it, Dad.

02:47.655 --> 02:49.837
Right now a free sink is
about all we can afford.

02:49.838 --> 02:52.571
Of course, we'll have to
take out all the formica,

02:52.572 --> 02:54.074
put in new formica.

02:54.075 --> 02:56.337
- It's a two-man job.
- I know.

02:56.338 --> 02:59.691
And this man's about maxed out.
My schedule's tight right now.

02:59.692 --> 03:01.483
What about that fella in there?

03:02.273 --> 03:03.639
- Who?
- [TV playing indistinctly]

03:03.640 --> 03:06.884
That guy on the couch. Is
there someone else in there?

03:06.885 --> 03:09.257
I'm talking about Axl.

03:09.258 --> 03:11.301
[Laughs] Axl?

03:11.302 --> 03:13.527
What, he's got something else going on?

03:13.528 --> 03:15.661
Nope, he's not back in
school for another week,

03:15.662 --> 03:17.322
but... it's Axl.

03:17.323 --> 03:20.017
We were excited when he moved
from his bed to the couch today.

03:20.018 --> 03:23.650
It sounds like you don't have
a whole lot of faith in him.

03:23.651 --> 03:25.323
Oh, no, I don't have any faith in him.

03:25.324 --> 03:28.671
But if you're feeling
lucky, it's worth a shot.

03:34.241 --> 03:35.586
<i>[Man speaking indistinctly]</i>

03:36.101 --> 03:39.913
Axl, we're gonna be tearing
up the old counters and sink.

03:39.914 --> 03:42.638
[Mouth full] Oh, that's
okay. I can turn it louder.

03:42.639 --> 03:45.100
Actually, I meant you and me.

03:45.101 --> 03:48.044
We're gonna fix the sink together.

03:48.045 --> 03:52.111
- Oh, okay, Grandpa, no problem.
- [TV turns off]

03:52.112 --> 03:54.002
<i>Frankie: Don't be too impressed.</i>

03:54.003 --> 03:56.159
<i>Axl started a lot of jobs like this.</i>

03:56.160 --> 03:59.611
<i>But he had a time-tested escape plan.</i>

04:00.129 --> 04:01.585
Oh!

04:02.327 --> 04:03.882
Forget it. I'll just do it.

04:05.298 --> 04:07.046
[Vacuum whirring]

04:07.047 --> 04:09.040
Forget it! I'll just do it!

04:13.106 --> 04:15.150
We need to take out the appliances,

04:15.151 --> 04:16.240
empty the fridge,

04:16.241 --> 04:19.452
- so we'll have an easier time moving it.
- Sure thing, Grandpa.

04:22.392 --> 04:24.470
[Whistling]

04:25.690 --> 04:27.845
[Loud clattering]

04:27.846 --> 04:28.747
Oh, no!

04:28.748 --> 04:30.436
Oh. [Blows raspberry] I'm no good at this.

04:30.437 --> 04:31.801
Should we forget it and you'll just do it?

04:31.802 --> 04:33.053
That's all right.

04:33.054 --> 04:35.844
Clean up that mess and we'll start again.

04:35.845 --> 04:37.900
Uh... [scoffs]

04:37.901 --> 04:39.792
Won't I just be slowing you down?

04:39.793 --> 04:42.360
I got all the time in the world.

04:42.361 --> 04:44.360
[Inhales sharply] Mm.

04:46.402 --> 04:47.225
[Door opens]

04:47.226 --> 04:49.632
- Oh, hey, look at that.
- [Machinery beeping]

04:49.633 --> 04:50.702
- Jim: Hey, Sue.
- [Laughs]

04:51.425 --> 04:54.159
This place is looking
sweet, Little Girl Mike.

04:54.160 --> 04:55.169
Thanks!

04:55.170 --> 04:58.418
I went with a whole
quarry-theme for the coffee area.

04:58.419 --> 05:03.276
We have sugar rocks, doughnut holes,

05:03.277 --> 05:05.211
and I hope you have a blast.

05:05.212 --> 05:07.545
[Laughs] Well, usually honey ticks me off

05:07.546 --> 05:08.585
on account of it being sticky.

05:08.586 --> 05:10.615
But putting it inside a straw is nice.

05:10.616 --> 05:12.377
[Door opens and closes]

05:12.793 --> 05:13.835
[Clears throat] [Beeping continues]

05:15.312 --> 05:16.557
Hey, Dad.

05:18.771 --> 05:20.711
So, what do you think?

05:20.712 --> 05:23.060
Uh... Sue, I think it's good

05:23.061 --> 05:24.193
that you're making an effort here.

05:24.194 --> 05:25.743
The coffee area's fine,

05:25.744 --> 05:27.411
but just keep in mind this
is a place of business.

05:27.412 --> 05:30.953
So I don't wanna see any... Bedazzling or...

05:30.954 --> 05:33.363
Or posters of kittens
being nice to each other

05:33.364 --> 05:35.371
- or anything like that, understand?
- Got it.

05:35.372 --> 05:36.534
Just give me a minute.

05:36.535 --> 05:39.383
I'm gonna go take something
down from the break room.

05:42.528 --> 05:44.555
[Lever rattles]

05:46.286 --> 05:48.856
Ugh! God, this place is a mess!

05:55.182 --> 05:58.239
"Old mother Hubbard's cupboard was so messy,

05:58.240 --> 06:00.149
"instead of cleaning it with a broom,

06:00.150 --> 06:02.061
she cleaned it with a blank."

06:02.062 --> 06:04.255
Not now, Brick. I gotta
make lunch for the guys.

06:04.256 --> 06:10.561
[Humming "Match Game" theme]

06:11.602 --> 06:13.619
- You know, I'm kind of in the middle...
- Five seconds.

06:13.620 --> 06:15.807
- I'm not gonna... three... Two...
- Shovel!

06:15.808 --> 06:17.899
- She cleaned it with a shovel!
- [Imitates buzzer]

06:17.900 --> 06:19.848
Sorry, Brett Somers said "rake."

06:19.849 --> 06:21.757
"Rake"? What was she, drunk?

06:21.758 --> 06:23.937
Look, I don't have time for weirdness now.

06:23.938 --> 06:25.760
I gotta go make a B.L.T. In my bedroom.

06:27.969 --> 06:29.247
Hmm.

06:31.512 --> 06:33.417
[Toilet flushes]

06:33.418 --> 06:34.933
So, listen to this,

06:34.934 --> 06:37.532
I was moving the dresser to toast some bread.

06:37.533 --> 06:42.283
Makes sense. And I found an
old paycheck from Ehlert Motors.

06:42.284 --> 06:49.052
For...$146.32!

06:49.053 --> 06:53.103
- ♪ $146... ♪
- Please, I work with Sue now.

06:53.104 --> 06:54.713
I've already seen so much dancing today.

06:54.714 --> 06:56.497
How crazy lucky are we?

06:56.498 --> 06:58.610
Well, the same crazy lucky as always.

06:58.611 --> 07:02.091
This is void after 90
days. No bank will cash it.

07:02.092 --> 07:05.002
Oh, crap.

07:05.003 --> 07:07.404
Wait, does this mean I
have to go back to Ehlert

07:07.405 --> 07:09.341
and ask him to reissue the check?

07:09.342 --> 07:10.604
[Groans]

07:10.605 --> 07:12.241
How badly do we need this money?

07:12.242 --> 07:15.232
I'm a nighttime cupcake delivery boy.

07:16.544 --> 07:17.642
[Sighs] Fine.

07:22.188 --> 07:23.905
Feels good, huh, son?

07:23.906 --> 07:24.956
Mm-hmm.

07:24.957 --> 07:26.655
It's amazing what you can get done...

07:26.656 --> 07:29.087
[Object clatters] When
you put your phone down.

07:29.088 --> 07:31.762
Can I, uh, get my phone back now or...

07:31.763 --> 07:34.042
Okay, I'm heading home for the night.

07:34.043 --> 07:37.797
I gotta soak my foot so I can
get it in my shoe tomorrow.

07:37.798 --> 07:40.038
We'll drop in the sink in the morning.

07:40.039 --> 07:43.752
- [Touch screen clicking]
- Got to find another screw like this one.

07:43.753 --> 07:46.244
Put in the faucet assembly.

07:46.245 --> 07:48.187
You, uh, going to the hardware store or...

07:48.188 --> 07:51.347
Why would I buy something we already own?

07:51.348 --> 07:52.488
Mmm.

07:52.489 --> 07:55.191
You find one tonight,
we can start first thing.

07:55.192 --> 07:57.286
[Chuckles] What?

07:57.287 --> 07:58.642
That's like a thousand screws in there.

07:58.643 --> 08:00.859
Gotta go through all that
to find one that matches?

08:00.860 --> 08:02.544
Aren't screws, like, 3 cents?

08:02.545 --> 08:04.313
That's 3 cents in your pocket.

08:09.537 --> 08:13.565
So, it's been a while, huh?
How you doing, Mr. Ehlert?

08:13.566 --> 08:17.341
I had a mole the size of
Texas frozen off my back,

08:17.342 --> 08:19.640
and I'm sitting on a hemorrhoid pillow.

08:19.641 --> 08:20.598
How do you think I'm doing?!

08:20.599 --> 08:22.647
[Chuckles] Well, you look great.

08:22.648 --> 08:24.779
Down, girl. I'm a married man.

08:24.780 --> 08:26.762
[Forces laugh] That's so funny.

08:28.894 --> 08:30.532
Anyway, um...

08:30.533 --> 08:34.996
I found a paycheck for $146.32,

08:34.996 --> 08:36.467
but it's expired.

08:36.469 --> 08:39.193
So, if you'll just issue me
a new one, I'll be on my way.

08:39.193 --> 08:41.542
Frances, you haven't
worked here in two years,

08:41.543 --> 08:43.720
and now you're coming to me begging for cash?

08:43.721 --> 08:45.115
Look, I just want what's owed me.

08:45.116 --> 08:48.090
You can make it a nice round number... $146.

08:48.091 --> 08:49.233
I'll forget the 32 cents.

08:49.234 --> 08:51.278
You know what else is a nice round number?

08:51.279 --> 08:52.406
Zero.

08:52.407 --> 08:54.476
- Mr. Ehlert...
- Frances...

08:54.477 --> 08:56.444
I give my charity at home.

08:56.445 --> 08:58.797
Well, actually, I don't give it there either.

08:58.798 --> 09:01.510
But if I were gonna give
charity... and I won't...

09:01.511 --> 09:03.789
I would certainly not give it at work.

09:03.790 --> 09:06.529
Now if you want your money,
you gotta come in and earn it.

09:06.530 --> 09:07.771
But I already did!

09:07.772 --> 09:09.730
I-I mean, I know I
didn't sell a lot of cars,

09:09.731 --> 09:12.054
but I made the coffee,
I stacked the brochures,

09:12.055 --> 09:13.432
I came to work on time.

09:13.433 --> 09:15.396
A-almost on time.

09:15.397 --> 09:18.478
Look, you're lucky you got me in a good mood.

09:18.479 --> 09:19.415
I'll tell you what,

09:19.416 --> 09:22.405
you come in this Saturday and work for me,

09:22.406 --> 09:23.319
and I'll give you the money.

09:23.320 --> 09:24.818
Now skedaddle.

09:24.819 --> 09:26.858
I've got a sitz bath in the men's room

09:26.859 --> 09:28.747
singing a siren song to my keister.

09:33.759 --> 09:35.355
<i>Man on TV: What a catch by Holland.</i>

09:35.356 --> 09:37.201
<i>I don't know how he held on to that.</i>

09:37.202 --> 09:39.820
<i>[Speaks indistinctly]
Mike Heck, come on down!</i>

09:39.821 --> 09:41.743
You're the next contestant
on "the price is right."

09:41.744 --> 09:44.175
Brick, I'm just trying
to relax for 10 minutes

09:44.176 --> 09:45.235
before my night shift.

09:45.236 --> 09:46.713
So where you from, Mike?

09:46.714 --> 09:48.143
I'm from this couch.

09:48.144 --> 09:49.422
That's my favorite part of the house.

09:49.423 --> 09:51.914
Now the game is "Higher Lower."

09:51.915 --> 09:55.032
Our first item up for bid
is Plum Blossom soy sauce,

09:55.033 --> 09:56.618
the soy sauce of emperors.

09:56.619 --> 09:59.484
We have this priced at $1.89.

09:59.485 --> 10:02.046
Is the actual retail price higher or lower?

10:02.047 --> 10:04.962
Brick, I'm not... Oh, hell, higher.

10:04.963 --> 10:06.686
[Sighs, imitates buzzer]

10:06.687 --> 10:09.573
The actual price of soy sauce is $1.65.

10:09.574 --> 10:11.441
But don't worry. You
still have a chance to win.

10:11.442 --> 10:12.745
I already lost.

10:12.746 --> 10:16.142
Cup-a-Hoosier noodle soup, now
with more chicken-like taste!

10:16.143 --> 10:17.960
We have it at $3.29.

10:18.371 --> 10:21.829
Ooh! Lower! Lower! Dad, trust me,

10:21.830 --> 10:24.208
<i>I killed it at "Joker's Wild" this morning.</i>

10:24.209 --> 10:25.199
[Clicks tongue]

10:25.200 --> 10:28.378
My daughter's saying lower,
so I'm gonna go lower.

10:28.379 --> 10:29.602
Ding, ding, ding, ding, ding!

10:29.603 --> 10:31.383
You go to the showcase showdown!

10:31.384 --> 10:33.155
[Whispers] Showcase showdown.

10:33.156 --> 10:35.030
[Normal voice] I gotta set it up.

10:35.031 --> 10:35.943
[Door opens]

10:36.737 --> 10:38.306
- Frankie: Aw.
- [Door closes]

10:38.307 --> 10:41.323
You got "The Price Is Right"? Lucky.

10:41.324 --> 10:43.165
[Sighs heavily]

10:43.728 --> 10:47.152
So get this. Mr. Ehlert
won't reissue the check

10:47.153 --> 10:48.975
unless I go in and work for a day.

10:48.976 --> 10:51.175
- What?
- Oh, yeah.

10:51.805 --> 10:52.627
[Sighs] It's fine.

10:52.628 --> 10:54.135
There are a couple new people there

10:54.136 --> 10:56.538
who don't know we used to
call him "Mr. Smell-ert," so...

10:56.539 --> 10:58.143
I'm gonna get that going
again before I leave.

10:58.144 --> 10:59.753
So, Dad...

10:59.754 --> 11:02.356
Did you tell mom how well
I'm doing at the quarry?

11:02.357 --> 11:06.327
- She's doing fine.
- Oh, Dad... Stop.

11:06.328 --> 11:08.046
No, I'm... I'm impressed.

11:08.047 --> 11:11.097
Once we got the no singing
rule down, it's been good.

11:11.098 --> 11:14.163
She's working hard, and the
guys enjoy having her there.

11:14.164 --> 11:15.832
Sue, look at you!

11:15.833 --> 11:18.145
I gotta say, I really love working there.

11:18.146 --> 11:20.085
And I think the place is shaping up.

11:20.086 --> 11:22.794
If I can find a time
when nobody's muddy boots

11:22.795 --> 11:23.629
are walking through,

11:23.630 --> 11:27.276
I am dying to get in there
and really get some of those

11:27.277 --> 11:29.024
gross stains off the break room floor.

11:29.025 --> 11:31.050
Well, if you're that excited about it,

11:31.051 --> 11:32.577
I can give you the keys.
You can go in this weekend.

11:32.578 --> 11:34.326
[Gasps] Oh, do not tease me.

11:34.327 --> 11:36.040
[Keys jangle]

11:40.492 --> 11:42.049
This looks good.

11:42.050 --> 11:44.658
- Nice and flush with the countertop.
- Mm-hmm.

11:44.659 --> 11:46.888
You dropped this in all by yourself, huh?

11:46.889 --> 11:48.500
[Chuckles]

11:48.501 --> 11:49.955
[Water continues flowing]

11:52.873 --> 11:54.371
- [Turns off faucet]
- Oh, my God, it's fine.

11:54.372 --> 11:55.881
It's better than what we had before.

11:55.882 --> 11:58.659
- I guess that's true.
- [Turns faucet on]

11:58.660 --> 12:02.108
So you like the water
coming out both sides, huh?

12:02.109 --> 12:04.128
Yeah, I like sideways water.

12:04.129 --> 12:06.092
You can fill two glasses
at once. It's awesome.

12:07.136 --> 12:08.966
And you used the right screw?

12:08.967 --> 12:10.941
What? There's, like, a
billion screws in there!

12:10.942 --> 12:11.894
It's close enough.

12:11.895 --> 12:14.178
And you think this is your best work?

12:14.179 --> 12:16.195
You're... you're happy with this?

12:16.196 --> 12:18.578
I am. I feel great about it.

12:20.599 --> 12:22.198
Then I guess you're done.

12:22.199 --> 12:23.636
I guess I am.

12:27.027 --> 12:28.270
[Groans]

12:28.961 --> 12:30.591
I don't get what the point of me learning

12:30.592 --> 12:32.454
how to put a sink in is anyway.

12:32.455 --> 12:34.138
I mean, I'm a business major.

12:34.139 --> 12:35.766
Why would I need to know how to do this?

12:35.767 --> 12:39.986
You need to know... So you'll know.

12:39.987 --> 12:44.606
Wha... what does that even mean?!

12:46.042 --> 12:48.797
Ugh. Nobody's in the
Arby's parking lot either.

12:48.798 --> 12:51.124
Should we just go back to the
Frugal Hoosier parking lot?

12:51.125 --> 12:52.800
[Sighs] Well, we gotta decide,

12:52.801 --> 12:54.892
or I need to get another
50 cents worth of gas.

12:54.893 --> 12:56.428
I don't just wanna do nothing.

12:56.429 --> 12:58.898
Now that I'm holding down two jobs,

12:58.899 --> 13:00.648
it's important for me to kick back

13:00.649 --> 13:02.244
and take some "me" time.

13:02.245 --> 13:04.299
Oh, I can't believe you work at a quarry.

13:04.300 --> 13:05.325
A quarry is so cool.

13:05.326 --> 13:06.572
What even is a quarry?

13:06.573 --> 13:08.390
Oh, it's amazing.

13:08.391 --> 13:10.432
It's this whole major operation.

13:10.433 --> 13:12.302
There's this... hey.

13:12.303 --> 13:14.922
I still have the keys on me.

13:14.923 --> 13:16.864
Do you guys wanna go see it?

13:16.865 --> 13:17.907
All right!

13:17.908 --> 13:19.313
Pop "Grease 2" back in its case.

13:19.314 --> 13:20.936
This saturday night just
turned itself around.

13:20.937 --> 13:22.462
[Chain clanks]

13:27.945 --> 13:28.653
Wow!

13:28.654 --> 13:30.778
Oh, my god! It's like the Emerald City,

13:30.779 --> 13:32.380
but more umber-y.

13:32.381 --> 13:34.390
It's like the Earth-Tone city.

13:34.391 --> 13:37.258
So there's the trailer
me and my dad work out of.

13:37.259 --> 13:40.095
And there's the high security area.

13:40.096 --> 13:42.379
Only certain people have access to it.

13:42.380 --> 13:43.934
I do. No biggie.

13:43.935 --> 13:44.895
Wow!

13:44.896 --> 13:46.280
We gotta insta this. [Gasps]

13:48.679 --> 13:49.852
Come on, come on.

13:53.538 --> 13:54.424
[Camera shutter clicks]

13:54.999 --> 13:57.034
Rockin'...At the quarry.

13:57.035 --> 13:58.863
- [Giggles]
- [Touch screen clicking]

14:00.429 --> 14:01.709
Hi!

14:03.545 --> 14:04.424
Do you work here?

14:04.766 --> 14:06.579
Oh. Sort of.

14:06.964 --> 14:08.854
I'm interested in that car.

14:08.855 --> 14:11.681
Great. You let me know when you decide.

14:11.682 --> 14:12.540
Either way, it's fine.

14:14.326 --> 14:15.258
I'm sorry?

14:15.259 --> 14:17.614
[Mouth full] Look, I
got no dog in this fight.

14:17.615 --> 14:19.468
Take the car, don't take the car. Whatevs.

14:21.533 --> 14:24.172
You know what? I think I'll take it.

14:25.365 --> 14:26.296
Wait. What?

14:26.297 --> 14:28.241
Well, assuming I like the price.

14:28.884 --> 14:31.013
Okay, look, I know this waltz.

14:31.014 --> 14:32.475
You'll come in with a number too low,

14:32.476 --> 14:33.594
I'll come back with one too high,

14:33.595 --> 14:34.652
we'll end up 5% below sticker,

14:34.653 --> 14:36.920
you'll walk away saying
you'll think about it,

14:36.921 --> 14:38.509
and you'll never come back, which is cool,

14:38.510 --> 14:40.062
'cause I'm never coming back either.

14:40.063 --> 14:43.156
5% below sticker sounds
great. You got a deal.

14:45.522 --> 14:47.530
- So where should we go next?
- Mm!

14:48.436 --> 14:49.911
Doug's Fancy Yogurt?

14:49.912 --> 14:52.796
Yogurt AprÃ¨s Pizza? Dairy Overload?

14:52.797 --> 14:53.636
I love it!

14:53.637 --> 14:54.647
[Laughs]

14:56.679 --> 14:58.091
Hey, you know where the party's at?

14:58.720 --> 15:01.783
What? Who are you guys?
What are you doing here?

15:01.784 --> 15:04.300
We saw something on Instagram
about a quarry party.

15:04.301 --> 15:08.066
What? What? No, no. No,
no, no, no, no, no, no.

15:08.067 --> 15:10.338
There is no party. You guys have to leave.

15:10.339 --> 15:13.132
You're not allowed to be here.
Nobody is allowed to be here.

15:13.133 --> 15:15.201
Oh, my god. Sue, look.

15:15.202 --> 15:19.036
<i>[Rock music playing]</i>

15:20.994 --> 15:23.580
Man: ♪ yeah, yeah-yeah,
yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah-yeah ♪

15:24.787 --> 15:26.160
[Door opens]

15:26.529 --> 15:28.839
Mike, look at this.

15:28.840 --> 15:32.961
Not only did I get my back
pay, but I made two commissions!

15:32.962 --> 15:34.820
<i>What? How'd you do that?</i>

15:34.821 --> 15:38.071
Okay. You know how Oprah's
motto is "live your best life"?

15:38.072 --> 15:40.092
Can't that woman just stay retired?

15:40.093 --> 15:42.973
Well, here's my motto now. "Don't try."

15:42.974 --> 15:44.764
I thought that was always your motto.

15:44.765 --> 15:46.167
I did, too.

15:46.168 --> 15:48.268
Turns out this whole time
I thought I wasn't trying,

15:48.269 --> 15:50.351
I was actually trying a teeny bit.

15:50.352 --> 15:53.051
The key is to not try at all.

15:53.052 --> 15:56.067
Ooh! Sue-mometer is heatin' up.

15:56.068 --> 15:57.228
Look at that.

15:57.229 --> 15:59.519
Orson Community College is in our sights.

15:59.520 --> 16:00.293
Whoo!

16:00.946 --> 16:02.638
♪ I feel all right ♪

16:02.639 --> 16:04.641
Please don't throw your
red cups on the ground!

16:04.642 --> 16:07.369
And please, those of you with bottles,

16:07.370 --> 16:09.085
put them in the green recycling bins.

16:09.086 --> 16:10.180
Great party, Sue.

16:10.181 --> 16:12.259
Oh, my god. A football player knows my name.

16:12.260 --> 16:14.002
Ah! Focus, Sue.

16:14.003 --> 16:15.171
Okay, you're right.

16:15.172 --> 16:18.546
Everybody! Everybody needs to go! Now!

16:18.547 --> 16:23.355
Please, please! If you could
all just follow me this way!

16:23.356 --> 16:26.309
Yep. This way!

16:26.310 --> 16:31.176
Hey, guys. Check this out. I
think you'll wanna see this.

16:31.177 --> 16:33.840
Brick, tell 'em what they've won!

16:33.841 --> 16:35.397
Mike and Frankie Heck,

16:35.398 --> 16:37.837
you have won a brand-newish sink

16:37.838 --> 16:39.358
chosen especially for you.

16:39.359 --> 16:41.146
[Plastic crinkles]

16:41.147 --> 16:42.513
[Frankie gasps] Whoa!

16:42.514 --> 16:44.479
Oh, I love this!

16:44.480 --> 16:48.818
We never win anything! This is great! [Gasps]

16:48.819 --> 16:49.815
Thanks, Dad.

16:49.816 --> 16:52.183
Don't thank me. Thank him.

16:52.184 --> 16:54.516
So... laying the formica was simple

16:54.517 --> 16:55.720
once you rough it out.

16:55.721 --> 16:57.961
The faucet can get tricky.

16:57.962 --> 17:00.283
Uh, the mistake a lot of
people make is cutting corners.

17:00.284 --> 17:03.194
You wanna make sure you use
the exact right set screw,

17:03.195 --> 17:04.385
which, of course, I did.

17:04.386 --> 17:07.353
And as you can see, the
water falls straight down,

17:07.354 --> 17:08.508
as opposed to other directions.

17:08.509 --> 17:10.723
Dad, can I get you a glass? Sure.

17:10.723 --> 17:14.282
Well, this is something. I
gotta get a picture of this.

17:14.284 --> 17:16.929
I know the fella at the store told me

17:16.930 --> 17:18.938
that there was a camera on here somewhere.

17:18.939 --> 17:21.101
Oh, yeah, you got it. Just
press the center button.

17:21.654 --> 17:23.715
Oh, this... This is too complicated.

17:23.717 --> 17:24.981
Here, why don't you take it?

17:24.982 --> 17:26.311
No, no, no, no, no. I'll show you.

17:26.313 --> 17:28.143
Then you'll know, huh?

17:28.941 --> 17:32.117
<i>Frankie: Yep, I sold two
cars, and we got a new sink.</i>

17:32.781 --> 17:34.433
<i>I don't get to say this very often,</i>

17:34.434 --> 17:37.672
<i>- but things were looking up for the Hecks.
- [Camera shutter clicks]</i>

17:38.388 --> 17:39.549
<i>[Cheering] Like I said,</i>

17:38.550 --> 17:41.551
<i>I don't get to say it very often.</i>

17:42.680 --> 17:45.061
Hey! Oh, no, no, no, no.

17:45.062 --> 17:46.223
Get out of there! Why are you...

17:47.179 --> 17:50.532
No, no, no, no! No dancing on the bulldozer!

17:51.665 --> 17:52.686
Oh! No, no, no, no!

17:52.687 --> 17:54.164
Stop it! Stop, stop, stop!

17:54.165 --> 17:56.467
You do not have security
clearance for that area!

17:56.468 --> 17:57.886
Sue, come quick. People are doing

17:57.887 --> 17:59.405
the polar bear dive into the quarry pen!

17:59.406 --> 18:01.129
Oh, my God. Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

18:02.760 --> 18:04.137
Carly? Oh!

18:04.138 --> 18:06.981
I'm sorry. He's in junior college.

18:06.982 --> 18:08.553
Oh, my god, oh, my god, oh, my god!

18:08.554 --> 18:11.044
Hey, check it out. I'm
the world's greatest boss!

18:11.045 --> 18:12.290
[Cheering]

18:12.291 --> 18:15.055
<i>No, you're not!</i>

18:15.056 --> 18:16.987
You put that down right now!

